From 8f7b97893b67ddc3264af282ce21004fb462dfa6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mpl_risk <dev@example.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 22:17:02 -1000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] feat: explicit calibrate(), optional click adaptation,
 error signalling, destroy()

Four small additions, all backwards compatible.

calibrate(x, y): adapt to a known gaze target without the debounce and
proximity heuristics that handleClick() applies to incidental clicks. Those
heuristics are wrong for a calibration routine, which knows the participant is
looking where it just asked them to click. The debounce is also rolling -- an
ignored click resets the timer -- so a sequence of calibration dots clicked
less than a second apart adapts only once, on the first dot. calibrate()
returns whether a gaze result was available to pair with the target, so a
caller can tell the participant to reposition instead of silently recording an
uncalibrated point.

adaptOnClick option and setAdaptOnClick(): the constructor unconditionally
registered a global window click listener that adapts on every click anywhere
on the page. Applications whose pages contain buttons, radios, or links have
every such click retrain the model toward that control. The listener reference
was also unreachable, so it could not be removed.

onError / {type:'error'}: an initialize() rejection inside the worker was
swallowed. 'ready' simply never arrived and the host could not distinguish a
slow model load from a broken one.

destroy(): terminate the worker and detach the click listener.
